result.formatted_address: 29, 30F, 239 Hennessy Rd, Wan Chai, Hong Kong
result.name: Pirata Hong Kong

reviews.text: It is a very nice restaurant. If I rate stars for the details... service 5 stars, food 4.5 stars, wine matching 4.5 stars, location 5 stars. The manager was really cheerful and kind to explain about the food and wine. And the other staffs were very nice too. The food taste and plating were very good. I ordered fork burn, tofu salad, yellow tail fish Carpaccio, fried egg plant, and Saint-Emilion wine. They were all good. Book in advance not to wait.

Very nice lunch. Great food. Wonderful views from the 30th floor. Our server Julie was impeccable
!..

Great restaurant! The service was splendid. The food was great! The menu was a combined menu where you could get dishes to share or order per person. Smaller portions. But if you get a 3 course you’ll be full. 

To find it, take the elevator to the 30th floor.
Had Easter brunch at Pirata and loved it. The staff were attentive and lovely with my daughter. The food was delicious and the drinks great too. Thank you for a fab afternoon.

Really top notch dinner. Artisanal theme with nuances that Europeans and locals love. Cosy, rustic, comfortable ambience and enjoyable skyline view. The vodka prosecco sorbet is a sensational finish. 
Service was decent given how busy it appeared. Chianti was nice too.
